            "brief_summary": "The purpose of this study is to test whether Fondaparinux is effective and safe to prevent thromboembolic events (like for example strokes) and bleeding events in patients who undergo a normalisation of their heart rhythm disturbance. Fondaparinux will be compared with Heparin and tablets containing Vitamin-K-Antagonists (Phenprocoumon, Fluindione, or Warfarin).",
            "eligibility_criteria": "Inclusion Criteria:\n\n* Male or female patients aged at least 18 years with atrial fibrillation (AF) meeting at least one of the following criteria (a, b, c): a. Acute clinical symptoms (like palpitations, chest pain, dyspnea, fatigue, lightheadedness, or syncope) for at least 48 hours and AF on base",
